    </name>

    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[
<p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;">
Write a Python program that uses clear variable names to calculate the final amount of an investment.
</p>

<p>Use these variables:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>initial_amount = 100</code></li>
  <li><code>interest_rate = 0.05</code></li>
  <li><code>number_of_years = 7</code></li>
</ul>

<p>Then calculate the final amount using this formula:</p>
<pre>final_amount = initial_amount * (1 + interest_rate) ** number_of_years</pre>

<p>Print <code>final_amount</code>.</p>

<p><strong>Expected output:</strong></p>
<pre>140.71004226562505</pre>
      ]]></text>
    </questiontext>

